qOcgIswpr6hokp5scikhH8Xc1SW42nQ0NwUjAFGhoNgjP2eIM0wkr2tOu1L0JGRjLdgcRn9kJ3s5zJwOFz1ufiSVMJDAMaooYjrOyX5DjLWObkUr6POJuKO4OxpzhQ\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying API dependencies**\\\\n\\\\nI'm working on an artifact that doesn't declare any Spring Kafka API dependencies, but it still returns or implements Spring Kafka listener interfaces. This raises a concern because the upstream compiles against version 2.8.0, and without this version, generated tests can't compile or use a meaningful API. I could argue for requiring version 2.8.0. Now, let's focus on crafting the final JSON while ensuring there are no Docker elements involved.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The target artifact is a Spring Kafka instrumentation library whose public API returns Spring Kafka listener interceptor types, but the published artifact does not declare Spring Kafka as a transitive API dependency.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\",\\n      \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"org.springframework.kafka:spring-kafka:2.8.0\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"The artifact exposes org.springframework.kafka.listener.RecordInterceptor and BatchInterceptor in its public API and upstream compiles this library against spring-kafka 2.8.0; without a Spring Kafka test dependency, generated tests cannot compile or meaningfully exercise SpringKafkaTelemetry.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No Docker broker or environment/system property is required for initial meaningful coverage. Tests can construct SpringKafkaTelemetry with OpenTelemetry.noop() or an SDK test instance, create record and batch interceptors, and exercise them with in-memory Kafka ConsumerRecord/ConsumerRecords plus a mocked or minimal Consumer where needed. Avoid adding producer-side KafkaTelemetry coverage unless explicitly testing the separate opentelemetry-kafka-clients instrumentation artifact.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"The library is named for Spring Kafka 2.7+, while upstream compiles against 2.8.0 to access newer interceptor methods; local Gradle/Native Image verification remains authoritative for the chosen dependency version.\\\",\\n    \\\"Full end-to-end Spring container or Kafka broker tests would require more setup, but they are not necessary to reach meaningful reachability coverage for the target library API.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0504a5bf4ac25c80016a3e76627ea88190bff16774f17a4113\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":19579,\"output\":1162,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":20741,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1782478421592,\"responseId\":\"resp_0504a5bf4ac25c80016a3e7655eea4819087a43a16d73a4b91\"}}\n./metadata/io.smallrye.reactive/mutiny/index.json:30:      \"2.8.0\",\n./metadata/org.apache.jackrabbit/jackrabbit-jcr-commons/index.json:82:      \"2.8.0\",\n./COVERAGE.md:1409:| `org.typelevel:log4cats-core_3` | [2.7.0<br>- 2.8.0](metadata/org.typelevel/log4cats-core_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> log4cats-core defines the core Scala typeclasses and data types for effectful, referentially transparent logging in Cats Effect applications. It provides logger, structured logger, logger factory, syntax, and no-op/extras utilities that can be used with different logging backends such as the separate SLF4J module.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.typelevel/log4cats-core_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:1410:| `org.typelevel:log4cats-slf4j_3` | [2.7.0<br>- 2.8.0](metadata/org.typelevel/log4cats-slf4j_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> log4cats-slf4j_3 provides the S